					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">3D objects have been done on the NES, though only in wire frame - see the game "Elite", as well as "Tank Demo" (same author).
<br />
<br />Texture mapping, however, is almost certainly out of the question, as it would require far too much CPU time and PPU bandwidth to be feasible.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
