					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">lord_Chile, I barelly understood what you said. It has nothing to do with the topic, but each name table is 960 (32*30) bytes long. Right after is the attributte table for that name table, and it's 64 (8*8) bytes long. Each name table + attribute table pair is 1024 (960 + 64) bytes, or 1kb long. The NES has 2kb of VRAM, so we get 2 name tables and 2 attribute tables. If that's what you were asking.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

